Android is transitioning from a 4KB to a 16KB page size, particularly on devices with 64-bit ARM processors
 - This change, driven by the hardware capabilities of many ARM CPUs,
 aims to improve system performance and efficiency by reducing overhead in memory management.

16 KB Google Play compatibility requirement
https://developer.android.com/guide/practices/page-sizes

